.Im MicroEmacs command|sql
.so me.tni
.TH sql-format 3
.XI sql-format - "SQL language, format SQL query"
.SH NAME
sql-format \- SQL language, format SQL query
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.na
.I n
.B sql-format
[ "\fIsql-query\fR" ]
.ad
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sql-format
creates a new  "\fC*sql-format-#*\fR"  temporary  buffer and inserts a formatted  form of the current kill buffer. The
formatting  process  attempts to make the SQL query more readable and manageable. The formatted  string is also copied
into the kill buffer, making it ready for pasting elsewhere. 
.PP
The numeric argument \fBn\fR can be used to change the default behaviour of the command, where the bits are defined as
follows:
.IP \fB0x01\fR
If this bit is not set the \fIsql-query\fR string is prompted for rather than using the kill buffer.
.IP \fB0x02\fR
If this bit is set then the reformatting takes the form of removing all excess  white-spaces,  reducing the query down
to a single line.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht sql 9 .
.ad
.FH
